<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE / 2000 4000 and 8000 MODELS BUILT OCTOBER 1, 1998 AND AFTER -
        SPEEDOMETER/TACHOMETER, GAUGES AND WARNING LIGHTS - 9800 - Troubleshooting - POWER DIVIDER LOCK (PDL) WARNING
        LIGHT, CIRCUIT, CLUSTER AND ALARM
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>POWER DIVIDER LOCK (PDL) WARNING LIGHT, CIRCUIT, CLUSTER AND ALARM</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s08245x_9.xml" xrefid="x0824518">Power Divider Lock (PDL) Warning Light and Alarm
                    <xref refid="x0824518"/>
                </hotlnk>
                for operation description.
            </para>
            <para>This light should come on for a bulb test during the Speedometer/Tachometer self-test process, then
                turn OFF.
            </para>
            <para>The light and alarm should be on when the power divider system is in operation.</para>
            <para>If the light works but not the alarm, skip Steps 1, 4 and 5. If the alarm works but not the light,
                skip Steps 3 and 6 through 12.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Testing PDL Warning Light, Switches, Circuit, Cluster And Alarm</title>
            <table id="t0824529">
                <title>Testing PDL Warning Light, Switches, Circuit, Cluster And Alarm</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="0" rowsep="0">
                    <colspec colname="1" colwidth="0.58in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" colwidth="0.58in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" colwidth="1.54in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" colwidth="0.96in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" colwidth="0.71in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" colwidth="0.92in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" colwidth="1.24in"/>
                    <spanspec namest="1" nameend="7" spanname="SPAN1"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES- IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Remove PDL bulb and test.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Bulb connectors.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Re-install bulb and go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace bulb.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Remove cluster connector (73). Measure voltage to ground at circuit 28B.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(73), 28B, to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>12&#177;1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 28B/ 13D from 10A fuse F4-A, then
                                    repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Disconnect connector (37). Measure resistance to ground at circuit 43-G.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(37), 43-G to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 43-G/11-GLA/11-GD, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>At connector (37) use a test lead to jumper circuit 43 to circuit 43-G. At
                                    connector. (73) measure resistance to ground at circuit 43.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(73), 43 to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Remove jumper. Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 43, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>5.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>With a good bulb installed, measure resistance between cluster (73) cavity 6 and
                                    cavity 18
                                    <hotlnk document="s08245x_27.xml" xrefid="f0824518">(Figure 18)</hotlnk>.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(73), cavity 6 to cavity 18.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Light path in cluster tests good. Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Open circuit in cluster. Replace the gauge cluster.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>6.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Measure resistance at PDL switch, across switch terminals* with switch closed and
                                    less than 10 PSI.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>Switch terminals.*</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Replace the PDL switch.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>7.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Measure resistance across switch terminals* with switch open and more than 35
                                    PSI.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>Switch terminals.*</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>>100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>If alarm still does not work, go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Replace the PDL switch and go to the next step if alarm still does not work.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>8.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Disconnect connector (434) and measure voltage to ground at circuit 28C.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(434), 28C to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>12&#177;1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 28C/13D from 10A fuse F4-A, then
                                    repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>9.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>At connector (434), use a test lead to jumper circuit 28C to 43C. Measure voltage
                                    at connector (73) circuit 28B to ground.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(73), 28B to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>12&#177;1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Remove jumper and reconnect connector. (434). Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Locate cause of low or no voltage in circuit 43C, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>10.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Jumper connector (37) circuit 43C to ground. Does alarm sound?</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(37), 43C to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Reconnect (37), and go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Replace alarm.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>11.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Disconnect connector (17). Measure resistance between connector (37) and (17) in
                                    circuit 43C and then circuit 43.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(37) and (17), 43C and then 43.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 43C or 43, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>12.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Measure resistance between connector (17) circuit 43C(+) and 43(-).</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(17), 43C and 43.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>&#60;3 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Circuits and alarm check good.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Replace connector (17) with diode assembly.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="7" spanname="SPAN1">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">*16 gauge Brown and 16 gauge Red wires when a PDL alarm is NOT
                                        installed. 16 gauge Yellow and 16 gauge Green wire spliced to circuit 43 when a
                                        PDL alarm IS installed.
                                    </emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
